comments.body:
@ipbabble.  Looks really good.  One last thing to drive you crazy with. In your examples in some places you have a command prompt, and others you do not.  I think you probably ought to have them in all, especially the ones where you've a mixture of running something and it's output (i.e. the docker container running sample).  Probably worth ask @jberkus about for a point of sanity.

FWIW, I ran through the tutorial again on a new vm, it ran really nicely.

Will look at the CI fun.
